# Zettelkasten: atomic notes for learning and reference

## Structure
- Template: 🗓️ datetime (DDMMYYYY HHmm), h1 title, content, References
- Filename = h1 title (snake_case), flat directory
- One atomic concept per note

## Content

Two note types — pick one per note:

### Study material (default)
- Teach one concept clearly — optimize for understanding
- Lead with what it is and why it matters (big picture first)
- Include whatever helps learning: trade-offs, comparisons, when to use/avoid, pitfalls
- Skip what doesn't: no filler sections just to match a template
- Details, examples, and code go toward the bottom — don't front-load implementation specifics
- Keep examples focused — illustrate the concept, not boilerplate

### Cheatsheet
- Quick reference — optimize for lookup speed
- Syntax, examples, flags, common patterns
- Minimal prose, maximum signal
- Tables and code blocks encouraged

## Style
- Big picture first, details and examples toward the bottom
- Point form, short sentences, cut ruthlessly
- Bold key terms on first mention

## Headings
- h2/h3 only, never h4+
- Natural headings (not generic "Why", "When")
- Prefer h3 subsections over bolded list items

## Linking
- Inline naturally: "See [[other_note]] for X"
- NO "because..." explanations on links
- NO "Related Concepts" sections
- Link only when: prerequisite, contrast, or logical next step
- Only link to notes that exist

## Admonitions
- Max 2 per note
- Types: `ad-warning`, `ad-danger`, `ad-example`
- Keep concise (1-2 sentences)

## Accuracy
- Verify before writing; cite sources for complex information
- Only link to notes that exist

